<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 06 at 11:28PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...SNOWFALL RATES OF UP TO AROUND AN INCH HOUR...
HAZARDS...Areas of heavy snow which can rapidly reduce visibility
to less than a half of a mile. Snowfall rates of around an inch
per hour,
LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...Areas of heavy snow will move northeastward
across the southern Adirondacks, Lake George Saratoga Region, Mohawk
Valley, Schoharie Valley, and the greater Capital District.
This includes Interstates 88, 87 and 90.
SAFETY INFO...
Conditions can deteriorate rapidly in winter weather situations. Be
prepared for snow covered roads. Slow down and allow extra time
to reach your destination.</description>
